abstract: "DTQEM v38.2 provides a robust and accurate inversion framework for extracting magnetic field strength B from the Zeeman splitting of the hydrogen Balmer‑alpha line (Hα, 656.28 nm). The model assumes a symmetric Gaussian triplet (π, σ⁺, σ⁻) with a fixed branching ratio, linear background subtraction, and Poisson negative log‑likelihood. Inversion uses differential evolution followed by L‑BFGS‑B. AICc with adaptive SNR‑based threshold selects between a single‑peak model (no field) and the triplet. A multi‑start parametric bootstrap (30 samples, 10 restarts, 10% perturbation, 20% fully random starts) achieves 100% success rate in validation tests, providing realistic 95% confidence intervals (e.g., 0.086 T at 1.0 T). The code includes extensive validation (synthetic spectra, stress tests, recovery curves) and publication‑ready diagnostics. Performance: relative error <2% for B ≥ 0.5 T, detection limit ~0.15 T, runtime 8–13 s per spectrum. The software is open‑source, written in pure Python, and suitable for laboratory, solar, and astrophysical applications where only intensity spectra are available."
